name: OYO 1762 Hotel Astiti Graha Tanah Lot
address: Jl. Tanah Lot No.264, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Avoid this "Hotel" even if you're extremely short on money. This place is not a hotel. It's considered a condominium complex. A local is sharing a room for tourists and charging double. My wife booked this hotel from the "Agoda App". She paid "117,000 IDR" then we got to the location there was some dude who spoke with my wife then he got someone on the phone who checked our reservation and then asked for more money and only pay in cash. My wife paid another "30,000 IDR". Please don't stay here by yourself based on other reviews. Also to note. Google Maps showing location in the wrong area to drive to this location. We drove around multiple areas to try to find the location. We even asked a local business and they never heard of this place. My wife was freaked out by the dogs roaming around the place. The wife states there was Free WiFi here. But after testing it's not fast enough to even upload vacation photos to the cloud. So I told the wife to remove herself from the WiFi for her safety. The bathroom isn't sanitary enough to go to the bathroom for a woman or take a shower for anyone. Sorry for the owner but this isn't a hotel. They are just using Google Maps as a free horrible Airbnb. Keep your money. Sleep in your vehicle if you have to.
review 2: They are thieves. After booking on agoda and I paid for 2 days after one day they said to me to check out and this price on Internet wasn't enough and it is enough for only the first day.. I already checked out after one day while my booking is for 2 days... After searching I found that this is common in Oyo hotels, you book online with a price and after going to the hotel they are asking for more... Avoid this hotel and any hotel related to Oyo
review 3: The room is reasonably nice, the price is very low, and the location is very convenient. The staff seem quite nice as well. On the downside the pool is currently out of order, there is no hot water,   no lockable storage area for luggage, and no refrigerator. Most other places I've stayed in Bali have had these amenities so that was disappointing. Overall I think the place isn't bad, but you definitely get what you pay for.
review 4: 1. When we arrived, they asked us to pay 100k more which is illegal but it seems like they don‚Äôt care, they know that we don‚Äôt have time to waste.                                          2. I ordered a 1 double bed and they gave us a room with 2 separate beds.
review 5:
Last time I apply oyo at Astiti hotel hali a remote one with very beautiful photos view, the actual is very very bad. I paid but prefer to cancel occupying although non refundable. And get better one similar price without oyo
Please update the photo for oyo‚Äôs benefit

name: Nyantra Caf√© & Eatery
address: Jl. Tanah Lot No.88, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: One of the nearest cafes from my house. I ordered Spaghetti bolognese, smoothies bowl, chicken wings, and they were good. The staff is nice, the venue is spacious also and it has beautiful rice field view. The parking area is decent as well.
review 2: One of the nicest looking restaurants I've been too. Very open space, lots of natural lighting and you feel the air. Food was really good and presentation was spot on. Prices were a little higher than average but for the building size and decor you'll forgive. A must try when in Tanah Lot
review 3: Nice place over looking rice fields and beyond very relaxing atmosphere the food is above average nice place to relax over lunch in a cool setting to get away from the heat
review 4:
Very stylish place to dine or have a coffee, and the views are impeccable. On our first visit, we ordered a smashed avocado sandwich and a combo vegan bowl; we waited for quite awhile even though it wasn‚Äôt very busy, and when the combo vegan bowl came, we had to remind them that they‚Äôve missed out on three major components/ingredients in the dish - mushrooms, tofu and pumpkin seeds - and they had to take it away as they put it down, and when it came back, the pumpkin seeds were still missing. We would‚Äôve been ok with them just clarifying the change or lack of ingredients but there was hardly any communication.
As for the flat white, we could hear that the coffee machine (milk) steaming was overdone and sure enough when we got it the coffee was boiling. That aside, it‚Äôs an up and coming place to hang out, if they could install more fans around the upper decks and over the sofa areas that‚Äôll make it so much more comfortable for customers. All in all, looks the package but still needs improvement.
Views are stunning though, looking out to lush green rice fields, you just can‚Äôt beat it!! We wish them all the best for the future.
review 5:
While it's obvious that a lot of investment has been done in making a beautiful place in a nice location and buying good reviews on Maps few days ago; we hope that the owners choose to invest in proper staff.
There were only 2 people in the place. One cook, another waiter; neither of whom understand English. They did what they could, and for that we appreciate them. The food was mediocre. Juices were ok.
What we were truly shocked to see was that there were so many good (5 star) reviews of this place- turns out they are all fake (bought) to compensate for the earlier bad reviews.
Hope the owners realise that buying fake reviews is not going to make their restaurant better and they learn to invest in proper staffing instead of online.
Your place is beautiful; but half of the menu items were not available (even though menu is already small); your staff (although try as they could‚ú®Ô∏è) is not equipped to deal with tourists; food quality needs to drastically improve- especially taste.
üôè [Please don't waste your money in buying fake reviews; kindly invest it in good efficient staff]

name: Warung Kampong Pedas Tanah Lot
address: 93MQ+VX3, Beraban, Kediri, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
I had a long wait for my order (about half an hour). The dish itself was very over-salted and ended up giving me diarrhea after 2 hours. Bingo collected.

Obviously I don't recommend this restaurant! Take care.
review 2:
Much of the experience was ordinary by Bali standards, but the part of the experience we most enjoyed was the beautiful surroundings.

F&B was slightly above average, service was a little hit-and-miss. Service was kind of slow. Prices alright.

View made it all worth it though.
review 3:
The place has a very nice view and relaxing atmosphere. I must say the foods can be improved. We ordered the ayam bakar madu, bebek betutu, tuna satay, etc. The marinade can be more flavourful. The chickens were a bit dry.

I am sure if they improve the foods, this place will be a big hit.
review 4: Good foods and services. The place was clean and spacious, with the view of paddy fields.
review 5: This is the nearest restaurant to Tanah Lot bus parking lot which offers very nice view of paddy field. There is also live music sometimes üé§ The food is delicious, especialy Balinese sate lilit üç¢ with sauce and sambal matah, that with one portion of rice is never enough üçö Eating with the nature view is always comfortable. I think they just need to add more space for parking.

name: Bebek sari uma
address: 93PW+88C, Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Nice Restaurant Near Tanah Lot Temple

We were hungry and accidentally found this place. They have quite wide parking and dining area. Even they have coffee plantations. They restaurant itself located beside the rice field, so people can enjoy meal while seeing the beautiful view. It will be great if you come when the sunset time. We ordered their signature menu Crispy Duck, Duck Fried Noodle, Satay Ayam, and Marakel. And everything was perfect, especially the duck. It was so crispy but very juicy inside. The satay also very nice with the peanut sauce. Best restaurant around here, very recommended. Keep it up. Thank you
review 2:
A good spot for food before heading to tanah lot temples. While the rice paddies view is beautiful and the food is as good as expected, the price is also more for tourists. (120k for ayam bebek)

We only saw tourists there so take that as you view.
review 3:
We really loved this place and grateful our driver recommended it. We toured the vegetation and then learned about the Luwak coffee making process.
Then we did a coffee and tea tasting - everything was delicious!
We stayed for lunch and got the crispy duck - it was delicious!!!!!
review 4: Very nice place to have Lunch. Duck is amazing, they have a big section of tee and coffee. I recommend the avocado coffee.
review 5:
One of the best hidden gem in Bali! Will definitely come back. It‚Äôs on the way to Tanah Lot and the food is so worth it. Duck rices are around 115-125k rupiah but the portions are huge! Duck is crispy good and not smelly.

They also offer free tea and coffee testing. Such an amazing experience! The Luwak coffee is 50k/cup and the other coffee/tea is 20k/cup.

The place is so serene and nice with gentle breeze  and perfect view. Its not hot and super great to spend the day in.

Overall perfect! I wish this place get a lot more exposure and visitors.

name: Sari Amerta Luwak Coffee
address: Jl. Tanah Lot No.264, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Great Sales people in this place and the 14 tea/coffee sampling are must have in a hot day. They know very well of how to do business by capturing your 5 senses. Be careful only spend within your budget. Anyway, all the merchandise
review 2:
the 14 tester is free..
my favorite one is the mangosteen and red ginger
the other is too sweet for me

i got coffee luwak, the taste is lighter, less sour, less bitter than the normal bali coffee.
good combination with fried banana

beside the coffee and tea they have shop selling chocolate and incense, etc

the staff very helpfull and give the information well, she welcome me in the parking, tell me about the place, show me the coffee tree, cacao tree, etc.
review 3: An unexpected delight, Sari Amerta Luwak Coffee Plantation offers a unique exploration into the world of Luwak coffee. Despite a rushed start, the friendly guides and variety of coffee and tea tastings, especially the delightful avocado coffee, make up for it. Set amidst stunning rice fields, it's a serene stopover en route to Pura Tanah Lot. Word of caution: souvenir shop prices can be high compared to local rates. A complimentary home kit would make the tour even more memorable. Recommended for coffee lovers and curious travellers.
review 4: We didn‚Äôt eat here but stopped to sample their homegrown tea and coffee! Got a sample tray and it was delicious! Highly recommended stop!!
review 5: Visited on recommendation of day driver. This place offers a nice tour followed by tea and coffee tasting. The souvenir coffee and tea are a bit on the pricey side but still seems to be worth it, given the good service of the team who took us around.

name: Nu Delhi @ Tanah Lot
address: Opp. Tanha Lot parking entrance, Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: very simple and hearty vegetarian Indian Cuisine. well priced and  delicious!  highly recommend
review 2: Home away from home. Great hospitality and delicious food. Being away from home, I thought any Indian food would be a treat. However, this restaurant‚Äôs food was actually flavorful and like homemade food. We had dosas, salted lassi, dal tadka, naans and an exclusive homemade papad!
review 3: Nice experience indian food. We tried Samosa, Jeera Rice (herb rice), Dal Tadka (potato soup), Plain Dosa and Masala Chai. These are vegetarian food with no garlic and onion content üëç
review 4:
It‚Äôs a great place if you are from
India and looking up for good Indian food. For me it was a blessing as i am pure veg had Dal tadka, chapati and masala tea felt like having food at home.
review 5: Food is good . I tried dossa masala and Chile bhature

name: Abian Bali Lucky Luwak Coffee & Warung
address: Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Wonderful! Must stop by if you‚Äôre otw to/from Tanah Lot! You get free coffee and tea tasting with explanation from the lovely staff! Monica was so nice and kind and the place has lovely rice paddy views. Highest recommendations!
review 2:
Nice spot to enjoy a quiet Luwak Coffee, with a little education on the Luwak Coffee steps.
The coffee and tea tasters were amazing with some fascinating flavours.
Staff were super friendly.
review 3: Lovely experience in the middle of the rice terraces. Great coffee and tea tasting and the option to buy some. Lively atmosphere, friendly staff and great products. Definitely recommend if you're in the area
review 4: Nearest tanah lot, nice view for taste coffee, important this free entry(others place will charge) . By the way, still buy my favourite luwak coffee.
review 5: Great place to come and sit. Free tasting of everything and coffee is great, especially loved all the information and history which was presented to us, seeing all the animals here as well was fantastic. Lemongrass tea is amazing

name: Warung Bu Andika
address: 93MQ+CF9 Areal Parkir Wisata, Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia

name: Gerbang Tanah Lot
address: 93MR+HC8, Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia

name: Warung Deepika By JIB Fusion
address: Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: We visited Tanah Lot temple and on the way back went to Kurnia seafood which also had Indian food options. It looked like a tourist trap with pricey food but luckily the service was too slow and we started looking for options when we came across Warung Deepika. I am so glad we went there. The service was quick and the food tasted amazing. We ordered vegetable murtabak and kadai vegetable curry and both were delicious. Highly recommend this place for Indian food.
review 2: I just had a blast of taste of Indian spices in my mouth. The food is so good and much better than you can find in more expensive places in Canggu area, for example. It‚Äôs simple, tho. And toilet can be improved‚Ä¶
review 3: Today i dined at a this restaurant in Bali that exceeded all expectations. The Indian cuisine was simply outstanding - from the flavorful naan to the delectable chicken and vegetable curry, each dish was a culinary delight. The restaurant's proximity was convenient, and the warm hospitality added to the overall experience. Five stars without a doubt!
review 4:
I ordered Chanai with plain curry and I love it! The curry is thick but taste mild, the spices are rich but doesn‚Äôt make your tongue sick. You will get big chanai with good price. Better to eat when it‚Äôs still warm. The place is close to Tanah Lot temple. You should come when you pass this area. Definitely worth it if you love Indian foods.

Ps : It‚Äôs a small place, don‚Äôt drive too fast 500mtr before you enter Tanah Lot temple gate, they are on the left side!
review 5: Very sweet people and the visit was totally worth it. We had very well made chai, samosa and thalis and it felt totally home made. Elissa is a very pleasant host, we got a very warm welcome by the team.

name: Harvest Palace, Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kediri, Tabanan
address: Unnamed Road, Beraban, Kediri, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82121, Indonesia

name: Sari Uma
address: Jalan Raya Tanah Lot Banjar Batu Gaing, 93PW+G5X, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Food came in great portion. It was delicious. The crispy duck combined with urap and the sambal. Fish crackers on the side made it perfect. It took some time for food to came out. The place is surrounded by rice fields and when we were there, they were burning some stuff and it got quite foggy by smoke. There‚Äôs no air conditioning but it‚Äôs very much shaded. Parking was limited.
review 2:
Lovely place to stop
Stopped on our way to temples, service was great - mini tour/explanation of process
Provided with a coffee paddle of about 16 different teas/coffee to try - they were absolutely wonderful
I don‚Äôt even like hot coffee but got the luwak coffee and it was great.
Beautiful spot as well - open looking over the fields

Great little shop to buy anything you want to take home and was all a very fair price
review 3: The Crispy Duck is amazing! Must try it. The ambience as fantastic and it is right in the middle of a rice fields. Best time to go is late afternoon and after.
review 4: This place is amazing. A nice restaurant and cafe near the road. They have very limited tables but they service are great. The foods are delicious. Fresh air and a nice rice field view. They also served us free drinks tea and coffee platter. It‚Äôs so amazing. I like this place very much and recommend for you all to give a try.
review 5: Went here for lunch after exploring Tanah Lot Temple and was pleasantly surprised by what they offered. Right as we sat down we were offered a free 13ish cup taster of all the different teas and coffees they had for sale, which you can buy by the cup or packets for souvenirs. A multi language information flyer was also provided explaining the different teas and coffees. Although the food and drinks were quite expensive (prob because it‚Äôs near a tourist attraction), the food was large in portion and very tasty. The view of rice paddies that complimented our lunch was also very incredible. Staff was also very friendly and parking was very spacious. A very recommended stop after visiting Tanah Lot Temple!

name: Pure Veg Delhi restaurant

I have no doubt when to eat here. Clean

review 3: Food was tasty, service kind and friendly and a good ambience.

name: IGOR TALOT Agro Resto
address: 93MQ+8XW, Jl. Tanah Lot, Beraban, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Good relaxing view of the rice farm. Meals are reasonably priced with mediocre taste, nothing special other than the scenic farm view. One good thing is it‚Äôs very close to tanah lot entrance.
review 2: This place is not just a restaurant, you can enjoy the unique decorations, enjoy fresh air with amazing rice fields view. The fish was great. Friendly people. Totally recommend this place to eat and chill. It is a waking distance to Tanah lot temple.
review 3:
Food was very tasty and the chicken well cooked and fresh, all with a peaceful view on rice fields and hills. They are having a large terrace/garden with a lot of seats and nice traditional decorations .
Highly recommended!
review 4: Beautiful place and beautiful people. Dinner was also perfect and made with heart‚ù§Ô∏è Thank you for the great evening and fantastic hospitality!
review 5: Owners stayed open late for us so we could drink beer and sit on their elevated patio and watch a thunder storm roll through the rice paddies from a hammock. Served bingtang in frosted mugs. Owners were incredibly friendly. Would highly recommend.

name: JERO TAMAN KOST
